author: @generationwolves
text: At 14:32, you can avoid the conditional statement to prefix 0 for single digit months if you format the string. For example: >>> "Month {:02}".format(6) 'Month 06' >>> "Month {:02}".format(11) 'Month 11'   Alternatively, you can also use str.zfill()  >>> "Month {}".format(str(6).zfill(2))                                        'Month 06' >>> "Month {}".format(str(11).zfill(2))                                       'Month 11'  ( https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/inputoutput.html )
